    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — the author's intent in its original context and its place in the canonical argument of 1 Samuel and the larger story of Israel's kingship. The movements below follow the chapter's three-part structure: David's gathering and prophetic obedience (22:1-5), Saul's paranoid court and the massacre of Nob (22:6-19), and the denouement of Abiathar's arrival and David's confession (22:20-23). Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens the meaning, a brief note follows each movement.",
